  Version:          0.18.0
  GitCommit:        fec3683
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>We can also check if the docker daemon is started with the following command:</p>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>systemctl status docker
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>You should get similar output like this:</p>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> docker.service - Docker Application Container Engine
   Loaded: loaded <span class="o">(</span>/lib/systemd/system/docker.service<span class="p">;</span> enabled<span class="p">;</span> vendor preset: enabled<span class="o">)</span>
   Active: active <span class="o">(</span>running<span class="o">)</span> since Fri 2019-12-13 23:27:50 CET<span class="p">;</span> 9min ago
